1Ô∏è‚É£ Using UNION
Q1. Combine employee names from Employees_2023 and Employees_2024 without duplicates.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT name FROM Employees_2023
UNION
SELECT name FROM Employees_2024;
2Ô∏è‚É£ Using UNION ALL
Q2. Combine product lists from two tables with duplicates allowed.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT product_name FROM Branch1_Products
UNION ALL
SELECT product_name FROM Branch2_Products;
3Ô∏è‚É£ Using INTERSECT
Q3. Find students who appear in both MathClass and ScienceClass.
Answer (PostgreSQL, Oracle):
sql
Copy code
SELECT student_id FROM MathClass
INTERSECT
SELECT student_id FROM ScienceClass;
4Ô∏è‚É£ Using MINUS / EXCEPT
Q4. Find customers who made orders last year but not this year.
Answer
Oracle (MINUS):

sql
Copy code
SELECT customer_id FROM Orders_2023
MINUS
SELECT customer_id FROM Orders_2024;
PostgreSQL/SQL Server (EXCEPT):

sql
Copy code
SELECT customer_id FROM Orders_2023
EXCEPT
SELECT customer_id FROM Orders_2024;
5Ô∏è‚É£ Using UNION with ORDER BY
Q5. Combine student names from two departments and sort alphabetically.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT name FROM Dept_A
UNION
SELECT name FROM Dept_B
ORDER BY name ASC;
6Ô∏è‚É£ Using UNION for different constants
Q6. Add a label to each dataset while combining them.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT name, 'Old' AS source FROM OldEmployees
UNION ALL
SELECT name, 'New' AS source FROM NewEmployees;
7Ô∏è‚É£ Using INTERSECT with WHERE
Q7. Find employees who work in both Dept 10 and Dept 20.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT emp_id FROM Employees
WHERE department_id = 10
INTERSECT
SELECT emp_id FROM Employees
WHERE department_id = 20;
8Ô∏è‚É£ Using EXCEPT with conditions
Q8. List products in Warehouse_A that are NOT in Warehouse_B.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT product_id FROM Warehouse_A
EXCEPT
SELECT product_id FROM Warehouse_B;
9Ô∏è‚É£ Union of different column values
Q9. Combine IDs from two unrelated tables using UNION.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT student_id AS id FROM Students
UNION
SELECT emp_id AS id FROM Employees;
üîü Using UNION with DISTINCT effect
Q10. Show unique cities from Customers and Suppliers.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT city FROM Customers
UNION
SELECT city FROM Suppliers;
